    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Indian architecture, a wall-offset flanking central wall-projection (bhadra); uparatha (Eastern India); anuratha (Oriyā); wall-projection between bhadra and karṇa parts, flanking bhadra; bay following the bhadra and succeeding pratiratha; subdivision in plan and elevation adjoining the bhadra.</Note_Text>
